The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                                       7                                                                                                        
	n Calcutta: With exactly 100 days to go for the ICC cricket World Cup 2011, the ICC Thursday announced the appointment of Sachin Tendulkar as the ambassador for the flagship event, according to a media release. The fact that the 2011 event will be staged here in the subcontinent makes it even more special for me, and I am keen to ensure we play well. As a team we would be doing everything we can to win the World Cup on home soil, Sachin said.        
	n Bangalore: Anil Kumble will be contesting for the Karnataka State Cricket Associations top job against current president Srikanta Datta Narasimharaja Wadiyar, the Maharaja of Mysore, on November 21. Venkatesh Prasad and Roger Binny will contest for the vice-presidents post. For the secretarys post, it will be a three-way battle between Jawagal Srinath, AV Jayaprakash and Siddalingaswamy.        
	n Calcutta: A minor fire broke out at the Eden Gardens on Thursday after the rag cover over CAB main gate caught flames from welding machine sparks. Though no one was injured, the incident could have spiralled into a disaster had the workers not doused the flames immediately.        
	n London: Chris Cairns has been given a green light by a court here to sue) Lalit Modi for posting a message on Twitter about dropping him from the IPL auction earlier this year.         
	n Sydney: Mitchell Johnson is to return to club cricket this weekend hoping to pick up a bit of form before the Ashes series.          
	n Gurgaon: Englands Laura Davies fired a seven-under 65 to take a two-shot lead on the opening round of the $300,000 Hero Honda Womens Indian Open Thursday.        
	n Paris: Andy Roddick, Tomas Berdych and David Ferrer secured the final three places for the season-ending ATP finals in London on Thursday. Roddick beat Latvias Ernests Gulbis 6-3, 7-6. In doubles, Mahesh Bhupathi and Max Mirnyi reached the quarters.        
	n New Delhi: Bob Houghtons India suffered their fifth defeat in the last seven matches when they went down to Iraq 0-2 in an international friendly at Sharjah on Thursday night.        
	n Calcutta: Bhowanipore Club were promoted to the Premier Division of the CFL after they settled for a goalless draw with Police AC on Thursday.         
